# clip.art / ESY Relationship

clip.art delegates all content generation to ESY's API (api.esy.com). ESY handles provider routing, retries, quality scoring, HITL review, batch scheduling, cost tracking, image processing, storage, and metadata enrichment.

## Migration Status

The current codebase still has direct AI provider calls. These are transitional and will be replaced by ESY API calls:

- `src/lib/imageGen.ts` — Gemini generation (ESY replaces)
- `src/lib/dalle.ts` — OpenAI integration (ESY replaces)
- `src/lib/r2.ts` — R2 uploads (ESY replaces)
- `src/lib/classify.ts` — Auto-classification (ESY replaces)
- `src/lib/promptSafety.ts` — Safety filtering (ESY replaces)
- `scripts/seed-animal-clipart.ts` — Batch generation (ESY replaces)
- `app/api/generate/route.ts` — Becomes thin proxy to ESY API

When modifying generation pipeline code, note that it will be replaced by ESY. Avoid deep refactors of generation logic — focus changes on the consumer-facing side (UI, SEO, display).

